<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-05-04T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-05-04T05:00:00-05:00" n="847" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d847">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119E/12: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Special Mission at
                                        Lausanne</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract—Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lausanne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-05-04T11:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 4,
                                            1923—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 5—6:14
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>290. Mission’s 278 of May 2 and 286 of May 4. Rumbold with good grace
                                has abandoned his opposition to participation in the work of the
                                subcommittee by members of our Mission. Tonight<note n="9" xml:id="d847fn9">Apparently this telegram was drafted on the
                                    night of May 3.</note> he sent his legal expert to ask who would
                                represent us in the meeting of legal experts tomorrow. Tentatively,
                                I named Turlington. Now we shall be represented on all subcommittees
                                dealing with matters in which we have an interest.</p>
                            <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>